<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 19 at 6:59AM EST  by NWS Buffalo</headline>
<description>...A BAND OF VERY HEAVY SNOW WILL RACE ACROSS WESTERN NEW YORK...
At 657 AM EST, a band of heavy snow with near whiteout conditions
was located along a line extending from Barker to near Westfield.
Movement was east at 45 mph.
Locations impacted include...
Buffalo, Rochester, Greece, Cheektowaga, Irondequoit, West Seneca,
North Tonawanda, Jamestown, Clarence, Chili, Lockport, Lackawanna,
Batavia, Kenmore, Depew, Amherst, Tonawanda, Olean, Geneva and
Dunkirk.
This includes the following highways...
Interstate 390 between exits 4 and 12.
Interstate 90 between exits 61 and 42.
Interstate 86 between exits 4 and 33.
Visibilities are near zero in this band of heavy snow. Significant
blowing snow is also occurring. The snow can accumulate at a rate of
one to two inches per hour or more in this band of heavy snow. Be
prepared for hazardous driving conditions. Consider delaying travel
if you will be going through this band of heavy snow.</description>
